Go-Go Boots is the title of the upcoming Drive-By Truckers \&quot;R&amp;B murder\&quot; album and is set to be released in the United States on February 15, 2011 and a day earlier elsewhere. This will be the Drive-By Truckers\' ninth studio album (eleventh total). The album was recorded over three blocks of sessions resulting in 25 songs, which the band decided to split between The Big To-Do and its follow up Go-Go Boot\'s. After The Big To-Do\'s release, the band continued working on and tweaking the album throughout 2010. Go-Go Boots marks the eighth Drive-By Truckers album produced by David Barbe. Wes Freed will once again be providing the album artwork.

Guitarist and frontman Patterson Hood has described the album to be the band\'s \&quot;most different and most Muscle Shoals sounding album.\&quot; The Drive-By Trucker\'s will include two covers by fellow Muscle Shoals artist Eddie Hinton on the album.
